---
description: Mandatory environment setup and validation workflow for AdonisJS
alwaysApply: true
---

# Environment Requirements

This project MUST always use Node.js 24, installed via NVM on WSL.

Cursor may not auto-detect Node, so every command that depends on Node.js, npm, npx, AdonisJS, TypeScript, tests, build tools or linting MUST first load NVM and activate Node 24:

```bash
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm"
[ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && . "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh"
nvm use 24
```

# Mandatory Validation After Every Code Change

After creating, modifying, refactoring code, generating files, updating configs, changing dependencies or editing tests, run the full validation pipeline before considering the task complete:

```bash
bash -lc '
export NVM_DIR="$HOME/.nvm";
[ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && . "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh";
nvm use 24;
npm run lint &&
npm run typecheck &&
npm run build &&
node ace test --parallel
'
```

# Failure Handling

If ANY step fails: stop, analyze the error, fix it, then restart validation from the beginning. Repeat until all steps pass. Never continue while validations fail.

# Completion Criteria

A task is complete ONLY when lint, typecheck, build and tests all pass. Do not claim completion without running these validations.

# Response Requirements

After code changes, always report:

```text
Node: v24.x.x
Lint: PASS
Typecheck: PASS
Build: PASS
Tests: PASS
```
